examples.en: I feel lousy today.
The food was lousy.
It's a lousy, rainy day.
They did a lousy job.
I like the work, but the pay is lousy.
He is still stuck with that lousy car.
I'm lousy at tennis.
He plunged his lousy head in the pillows.
What lousy weather!
The town was lousy with tourists.
He was a lousy husband.
That's a lousy way to treat a friend.
He drank too much and felt lousy the next morning.
Brenda's lousy with kids.
He left me a lousy fifty cent tip.
After complaining about the hotel's lousy service, the woman went off on another rant about the condition of her room.
She got lousy grades in high school.
A great actor who lavished his talent in lousy movies.
One lousy smacker was all she left for a tip.
She couldn't resist a parting shot (=one that you make just before you leave) - 'And you were a lousy lover!'
We were misguided by the flashy advertisements for what turned out to be pretty lousy pizza.
